The paper focuses on the task of question answering over personal narratives, which involves machine reading and reasoning in simulated worlds. This task involves natural language processing and artificial intelligence, which are both covered by the cs.CL and cs.AI sub-categories. The paper also evaluates several state-of-the-art QA models, which falls under the cs.LG sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval and search, which is covered by the cs.IR sub-category. Finally, the paper introduces a new dataset and framework for generating additional worlds, which falls under the cs.SD sub-category.
